CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 6, 1957, pg. 18 reads: "3. The New Diamond Market booth proved to be a popular one with the homemakers. Reason: Delicious samples of smoking hot wieners and hams.  Representatives are Ray H. Ross, "Red" Katzback and hostess, Gladys Randal."
TitMainTitle: Ray H. Ross, "Red" Katzback, and Gladys Randal standing in New Diamond Market booth in Syria Mosque for the 1957 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair
